{
  "texts": [
    "If L is charged (uncharged) under a fixed choice of D 0, then it must be modified to a line operator L ′ uncharged (charged) under the same choice of D 0.",
    "Thus a there is a single possibility for an irreducible 1-charge lying in twisted sector of2.",
    "This 1-charge comprises of a multiplet of two simple line operators L and L ′, such that the action of (1) 2 on L and L ′ differs by a sign.",
    "Below we study two examples of 4d QFTs having this symmetry and anomaly structure, where only such twisted 1-charges appear.",
    "This not only is consistent with the above general result but also explains why the same physical phenomenon is observed in both theories."
  ]
}